{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 08:21:12.654018", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Control-plane and fabric health: All EBGP sessions between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and stable. Routing tables across the fabric contain the expected /24 leaf networks with correct next-hops. Inter-leaf/data-plane forwarding via the spines is functional.\\n- Host health: One host (pc_0_0) is misconfigured. It shares the same IP address as pc_0_1 and is in the wrong subnet for its connected leaf. As a result, pc_0_0 cannot reach its default gateway or any remote destinations.\\n- The initial host-to-host reachability test is misleading due to duplicate IP addressing and represents self-pings rather than end-to-end host connectivity.\\n\\nDetected Anomalies and Impact\\n1) Duplicate IP address and wrong subnet on pc_0_0\\n- Evidence:\\n  - pc_0_0 IP config: 10.0.1.2/24 with default via 10.0.1.1 (ip addr/route). Its connected leaf interface is 10.0.0.1/24 (leaf_router_0_0 eth2), so pc_0_0 should be in 10.0.0.0/24.\\n  - pc_0_1 IP config: also 10.0.1.2/24 with default via 10.0.1.1, matching its connected leaf 10.0.1.1/24 (leaf_router_0_1 eth2).\\n  - Ping tests:\\n    - From pc_0_0: ping 10.0.1.1 (its configured default gateway) fails 100% (cannot ARP because that gateway is on a different L2/subnet); ping 10.0.0.1 also fails (traffic attempts to use the wrong default gw).\\n    - From pc_0_1: ping 10.0.1.1 succeeds; ping 10.0.0.1 also succeeds via the fabric.\\n- Impact:\\n  - pc_0_0 is effectively isolated; it cannot reach its configured default gateway or remote networks.\\n  - Both hosts reporting the same IP (10.0.1.2) breaks end-to-end host-to-host testing. The automated reachability output shows both hosts as 10.0.1.2 and reports successful pings, but those are self-pings due to the duplicate address.\\n\\n2) Reachability tool false positive due to duplicate IPs\\n- Evidence:\\n  - Host-to-host test shows both pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 have “10.0.1.2” as their IP, and pings “succeed” in both directions with dst_ip=10.0.1.2. These are not end-to-end tests to a distinct remote address.\\n\\nFabric Control-Plane and Data-Plane Findings\\n- Leaf interfaces:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 eth2: 10.0.0.1/24\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 eth2: 10.0.1.1/24\\n- EBGP sessions (show ip bgp summary):\\n  - Leaves (AS 65200 and 65201) have 2 neighbors each (both spines), established, receiving 1 prefix (the remote leaf subnet) and sending expected prefixes.\\n  - Spines (AS 65100, 65101) have 3 neighbors (super-spine + both leaves), established. They have routes to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via their respective leaf neighbors.\\n  - Super-spine (AS 65000) has 2 neighbors (both spines), established, and has routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via spine_router_0_0.\\n- Routing tables:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 has 10.0.1.0/24 via spine 172.16.0.4.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 has 10.0.0.0/24 via spine 172.16.0.6.\\n  - spines have both /24s via their leaf neighbors.\\n  - super_spine has both /24s via spine_router_0_0 only (no ECMP installed).\\n- Additional observation: The super-spine selects a single next-hop (spine_router_0_0) for both /24s (no BGP multipath/ECMP shown). This is not presently causing a connectivity problem in this small topology.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Host misconfiguration on pc_0_0:\\n  - Incorrect IP/subnet and default gateway for its attached leaf.\\n  - Duplicate IP address with pc_0_1 (both configured as 10.0.1.2/24 with default via 10.0.1.1).\\n  - This prevents pc_0_0 from reaching its gateway and any off-subnet destinations and invalidates host-to-host reachability testing., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='d22ad1c0-a06f-40eb-b497-48a40ee97534'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
